<div class="heading resPageHeading">


























<h1 >Academic Activity</h1></div>

<div class="content stackparsys">










				
				<div class="resAccordion section">
























 


<div class="row">
    <div class="col-xs-12">
        <div class="panel-group accordion background-hidden" id="b1ca2569-6db6-4a61-8d3b-f12a11c19d48" role="tablist" aria-multiselectable="true">
			
				<div class="resAccordionControl" role="group" aria-label="Accordion Actions">
					<button class="resAccordionOpenAll">Open All</button> <button class="resAccordionCloseAll">Close All</button>
				</div>
				<script type="text/javascript">$(document).ready(function(){ initResAccordionControl("b1ca2569-6db6-4a61-8d3b-f12a11c19d48", true); });</script>
			
            
            <div class="panel panel-default">
                <!-- Accordion Heading -->
                <div class="panel-heading container-clipboard">
                    <h2 class="panel-title">
                        <a id="accordion-1597676957826-what-activities-will-occur-on-campus-this-fall-2020-and-what-will-be-virtual-" role="tab" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#b1ca2569-6db6-4a61-8d3b-f12a11c19d48" href="#accordion-content-1597676957826-what-activities-will-occur-on-campus-this-fall-2020-and-what-will-be-virtual-" aria-controls="accordion-content-1597676957826-what-activities-will-occur-on-campus-this-fall-2020-and-what-will-be-virtual-" aria-expanded="false">
                            What activities will occur on campus this Fall 2020 and what will be virtual?
                        </a>
                    </h2>
                    
                </div>
                <!-- Accordion Body -->
                <div tabindex="0" id="accordion-content-1597676957826-what-activities-will-occur-on-campus-this-fall-2020-and-what-will-be-virtual-" class="panel-collapse collapse" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="accordion-1597676957826-what-activities-will-occur-on-campus-this-fall-2020-and-what-will-be-virtual-">
                    <div class="panel-body ">
                        <div class="1597676957826 stackparsys">










				
				<div class="resText parbase section">


























<div class="res-text richtextContent background-hidden" id="41aaa57c-c8fc-4390-9d14-9b6019409acc" >

    <p>Arts, FEAS, Science and TRSM have indicated they will be fully virtual in Fall 2020 with no classes on campus and providing enhanced virtual experiences for students.</p> 
<p>FCAD, FCS and Law have indicated the need for hybrid programming with some limited on-campus activity complementing virtual activities.</p> 
<p>Those unable to participate due to their living arrangements or other travel or health related issues will be provided a virtual alternative.&nbsp;</p> 
<p>A guiding principle is that wherever activity can be done virtually and remotely, that will be the default mode of delivery. We are looking to keep in-person interactions at an absolute minimum and only moving forward with them if there is no online or remote alternative.</p>
    





</div>
<script>$(document).ready(function(){addCoursePopover("#41aaa57c-c8fc-4390-9d14-9b6019409acc");});</script></div>

				</div>

                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="panel panel-default">
                <!-- Accordion Heading -->
                <div class="panel-heading container-clipboard">
                    <h2 class="panel-title">
                        <a id="accordion-1597676959701-have-any-decisions-been-made-about-online-proctoring-and-student-assessment-in-general-" role="tab" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#b1ca2569-6db6-4a61-8d3b-f12a11c19d48" href="#accordion-content-1597676959701-have-any-decisions-been-made-about-online-proctoring-and-student-assessment-in-general-" aria-controls="accordion-content-1597676959701-have-any-decisions-been-made-about-online-proctoring-and-student-assessment-in-general-" aria-expanded="false">
                            Have any decisions been made about online proctoring and student assessment in general?
                        </a>
                    </h2>
                    
                </div>
                <!-- Accordion Body -->
                <div tabindex="0" id="accordion-content-1597676959701-have-any-decisions-been-made-about-online-proctoring-and-student-assessment-in-general-" class="panel-collapse collapse" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="accordion-1597676959701-have-any-decisions-been-made-about-online-proctoring-and-student-assessment-in-general-">
                    <div class="panel-body ">
                        <div class="1597676959701 stackparsys">










				
				<div class="resText parbase section">


























<div class="res-text richtextContent background-hidden" id="031b9653-0efb-4678-b979-9b8101f9119d" >

    <p>Given the wide scope of evaluation needs and assessment required across our diverse range of programming, we are encouraging departments to work within their faculties to best determine effective and appropriate evaluation approaches and we are continuing to urge faculty to explore alternatives to examinations.</p> 
<p>The virtual proctoring tool available for use at Ryerson is <strong>Respondus LockDown Browser</strong> <strong>and Monitor</strong>. This tool provides automated virtual proctoring using a student’s camera to monitor the student during an exam. Respondus LockDown Browser and Monitor are accessed through the D2L Brightspace quiz tool. Additional functionalities are currently being investigated. The tool has been assessed based on availability, data privacy, and security by the <strong>Virtual Proctoring Working Group</strong>, a committee with representatives from each faculty, CCS, the Test Centre, the Academic Integrity Office, the Office of the Registrar, and the Centre for Excellence in Learning and Teaching, reporting to the Keep Teaching Taskforce.&nbsp;<br> </p> 
<p>The Virtual Proctoring Working Group has created a <a href="https://docs.google.com/document/d/1mcS1e1jrey0rRqVCCDsrPH3beiBygzqh4Ep2OBH7GjE/edit?usp=sharing"><span class="sr-only">google doc</span>document with considerations <span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-file-word-o"></span><span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-external-link"></span><span class="sr-only">, external link</span></a>instructors should review before choosing to incorporate virtual proctoring in their courses, as well as an overview of each available tool. Virtual proctoring tools do not fully replace the integrity of invigilated in-person examinations.</p>
    





</div>
<script>$(document).ready(function(){addCoursePopover("#031b9653-0efb-4678-b979-9b8101f9119d");});</script></div>

				</div>

                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="panel panel-default">
                <!-- Accordion Heading -->
                <div class="panel-heading container-clipboard">
                    <h2 class="panel-title">
                        <a id="accordion-1597676968566-are-there-plans-in-place-that-look-toward-what-programing-delivery-and-access-to-campus-will-be-in-winter-2021-" role="tab" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#b1ca2569-6db6-4a61-8d3b-f12a11c19d48" href="#accordion-content-1597676968566-are-there-plans-in-place-that-look-toward-what-programing-delivery-and-access-to-campus-will-be-in-winter-2021-" aria-controls="accordion-content-1597676968566-are-there-plans-in-place-that-look-toward-what-programing-delivery-and-access-to-campus-will-be-in-winter-2021-" aria-expanded="false">
                            Are there plans in place that look toward what programing delivery and access to campus will be in Winter 2021?
                        </a>
                    </h2>
                    
                </div>
                <!-- Accordion Body -->
                <div tabindex="0" id="accordion-content-1597676968566-are-there-plans-in-place-that-look-toward-what-programing-delivery-and-access-to-campus-will-be-in-winter-2021-" class="panel-collapse collapse" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="accordion-1597676968566-are-there-plans-in-place-that-look-toward-what-programing-delivery-and-access-to-campus-will-be-in-winter-2021-">
                    <div class="panel-body ">
                        <div class="1597676968566 stackparsys">










				
				<div class="resText parbase section">


























<div class="res-text richtextContent background-hidden" id="fc4cddfc-48dc-4c6d-bfa8-ec306dd0024a" >

    <p>We have committed to having a window of at least 90 days for students, faculty, staff, and other Ryerson community members to get notification if they have to return to campus. In this regard, we are currently looking at the options for Winter 2021 and beyond and are creating flexibility in our planning to accommodate for situations which may see prolonged limitations to on-campus activity.</p> 
<p>Decisions will be communicated with as much notice as possible.</p>
    





